{
  "texts": [
    "Transformer-based models) • According to [70], developing a text classifier is a trial-and-error process.",
    "Therefore, Non-Deep Learning models can be an effective solution in the early stages of the process thanks to the reduced training time and the low computational effort requiredThe chosen models (i.e.",
    "RF, GB, and SVC) are popular algorithms in text classification [68].",
    "The models used are implemented using scikit-learn [71] with default parameters, splitting the IMDB dataset into 80% training instances and 20% (10,000) testing instances.",
    "The dataset is transformed via Bag Of Word (BOW), and only the 10,000 most common features are kept to have a less sparse matrix devoid of spurious features."
  ]
}